name: Ragnar Trail Hill Country - TX
intro:
Ragnar Trail Relay Hill Country-TX, presented by Salomon, in the Lone Star State will take place on the amazing trails located at Flat Rock Ranch — a great place off the beaten path outside of San Antonio. This venue boasts the perfect balance of challenging, technical running, and rolling trails.

Teams of 8 or 4 will conquer a series of three loops while taking in the natural scenic beauty of the surrounding area. The runner friendly single-track winds through groves of Texas Live Oak, over classic Hill Country limestone shelves, around granite boulders, prickly pear cactus, and yucca plants on its way to the ridgelines that look back onto Ragnar Village and the rolling Hill Country. This is classic Hill Country and some of the best trail running you will find in the Lone Star State.

Ragnar Trail Hill Country-TX is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Ragnar Relay Austin and Ragnar Trail Hill Country-TX and earn the 20 Gallon Hat Double Medal.
 

We love our military! 

If at least half of your team is made up of service members you qualify for a $100 military discount! Ragnar offers flexible team transfer options and a revised policy for last-minute deployments.

Call or email customer service for details: (801) 499-5024 OR customerservice@ragnarrelay.com

village:
Ragnar Village at Flat Rock Ranch is located in a large field in the center of the ranch. It is the heart and soul of the race. Since each trail loop begins and ends in the Ragnar Village, it is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop, you will return to the support of your teammates and the camaraderie of all the runners sharing:

  • Bonfire
  • S'mores
  • Food and beer garden (Friday night pasta dinner is included for each runner)
  • Billions of stars

Partners

Salomon - Demo a pair of Salomon shoes out on a loop, free of charge of course!

REI - Learn how to make the perfect camp cup of coffee, lounge in the REI hammocks, or try night writing for the first time! 

High West Whiskey - Pick up a wooden coin on the highest point of the course for a free sample of High West Whiskey!

Nathan - Get your photo taken with the What Color is Your Pee Banner! Nathan products for purchase as well.

CEP Compression - Learn how compression socks will speed up your reovery by talking with Kendall in the Merchandise Tent

Nuun - Electrolyte samples to keep you hydrated throughout the weekend

Bondi Band - Stop by the Bondi Band booth to purchase your moisture wicking headbands, armbands, and other must have running accessories

Elevated Legs - Pneumatic compression leg sleeves will help with your recovery. Come get your legs squeezed at the Elevated Legs tent.

Freak Brothers Pizza - Freakishly good pizza served 24 hours a day to keep you fueled between your runs!

Goal Zero Charging Station - Solar Powered batteries to keep your electronics charged for the race weekend

Schedule

The schedule will be posted closer to the event.
training:
Training by Salomon

At Salomon our goal is to inspire runners to go beyond the pavement and enjoy greater freedom to run anywhere. We believe that with some tips and training almost anyone can become a trail runner and run the Ragnar Trail Relay. We are here to guide you on your training journey as you prepare to run the Ragnar Trail Relay.

  • How to Fall When Running Trails
  • How to Run on Snowy or Icy Trails
  • How to Run in Mud
charity:
Hill Country is just around the corner. Make the weekend even more meaningful by fundraising for a Ragnar charity partner or your favorite charity on everydayhero, the official fundraising platform of Ragnar Relay Series! 

Simply go here (or click on the everydayhero logo above) and choose your favorite charity – it’s that easy!  Your fundraising page will be created and you can start making every step count.

To date, the Ragnar community has fundraised over 1 million dollars so let's keep it going! 

Questions? Email nonprofits@everydayhero.com.


Team RWB's mission is to enrich the lives of America's veterans by connecting them to their community through physical and social activity. Please email Donnie Starling (donnie.starling@teamrwb.org) for more information on how to get involved.

legs.name: Green Loop - Creekside Trail
legs.description: After leaving Ragnar Village on you will quickly find yourself in a wide tree filled grove. You might think you are hallucinating if you run past some longhair goats but you are not. This is where they hang out. Who knew? They picked a great spot because this quick little loop is a nice cool shaded spot. Enjoy the single-track and you’ll be baa-baa-back at the Ragnar Village in no time at all.

legs.name: Yellow Loop - Pipeline Hill Trail
legs.description: This trail has the most varied terrain and the best views of the entire course. It starts by skirting the edge of a limestone shelf and then starts to climb. After half a dozen switchbacks you will be rewarded with a view of Flat Rock Ranch below, but maybe it’s not so flat. Now with a big ole grin on your face you can start the quick decent back to Ragnar Village. This last two miles is fast but be careful, the trail shoots through a few spots where the trees get tight. So don’t wear a set of longhorns as your costume on this loop.

legs.name: Red Loop - Buckeye Canyon Trail
legs.description: This trail is fun. You’ll hit great single-track that moves like a rollercoaster and banks like a bobsled. Just paste a smile on your face and get moving.

travel.content:
Directions to Flat Rock Ranch

From San Antonio:
Take IH 10 West from San Antonio 45 miles to Comfort.  Take the first Comfort exit, State Highway 27 west. Continue approximately 1/2 mile to the flashing yellow light at the Y intersection of State Highway 27 and US 87 North (go to the right). Go 1/4 mile to the stop light and take Ranch to Market 473 East (to the right). Go one mile and take Flat Rock Creek Road to the North (left). The pavement ends four miles later at the gate to Flat Rock Ranch.

From Austin:
Take US 290 West from Austin to Fredericksburg.  At Fredericksburg take US 87 South  (left turn).  Continue 26 miles to Comfort. 1/2 mile South of the intersection of IH 10 and US 87 go East (left) at the stop light at Ranch to Market 473. Go one mile to Flat Rock Creek Road and turn North (left).  The pavement ends four miles later at the gate to Flat Rock Ranch. 

From Kerrville:
Take IH 10 East from Kerrville 16 miles to Comfort.  Take the first Comfort Exit, US Highway 87 South.  Continue approximately 1/2 mile to the stop light at the intersection of US 87 and Ranch to Market 473. Take Ranch to Market 473 East (to the left). Go one mile and take Flat Rock Creek Road to the North (left). The pavement ends four miles later at the gate to Flat Rock Ranch.

 

Address is 346 Flat Rock Creek Road for GPS. Note: some navigation systems show address 1.5 miles short of the correct location on Flat Rock Creek Road.

GPS coordinates for location of gate at FRR: 30.015501,-98.8705

Team Campsite

Each team will be able to pick a location to set up their team campsite in the Ragnar Village. Parking is close by and there will be a gear drop with trailers to haul your gear to the camping area. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ's, whatever.

We don't assign specific campsites but we do ask that your team takes up less than 300sq-ft.

Camping in the Ragnar Village is FREE to runners/family/friends/crew on Thursday and Friday night. Teams will be allowed into the venue on Thursday beginning at 4:00pm. No teams will be allowed into the Ranch after 10:00pm on Thursday night so please plan accordingly. There will be toilets and water available Thursday but no other amenities beyond that so there will be no food/coffee/beer/etc. until Friday. As always, you can cook using a propane stove but there are no campfires or cooking fires allowed in your campsite at any time.

Gates will re-open on Friday morning at 8:00am.

Teams that elect to stay on Saturday will have to pay $10 to Flat Rock Ranch for each person over 12 years of age.

RV’s and Campers

All RV spots have been reserved for the duration of the race. 

Rental Gear

Also, if you are traveling to Ragnar Trail Hill Country from outside the area and wish to rent camping gear for the event, we would suggest you contact the REI Austin Gateway store. Note, that rentals cannot be made more than one month out so please plan accordingly.

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your campsite into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $15/person for a team of 8! Don’t forget that you will need a power source. We highly recommend the Goal Zero Yetis.

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, October 17th to ensure delivery before the race!*

Campfires, Generators and Pets

Campfires are NOT allowed in the team campsites at ANY time. Ragnar will provide a bonfire and some s'more pits on Friday night but individual team campsite fires are not allowed at any time.

Generators are NOT allowed in your team campsite. We will have solar charging stations in the Ragnar Village for your i-thingys.

No dogs on the course. No dogs in the campsite. No dogs at the event. We love dogs too but this is a safety issue for participants and for the dogs.

See the Trail Guide for a list of other things that are/aren't permitted in the campsite.

Sustainability

Ragnar seeks ways to reduce the carbon footprint of our races. We ask you join us in this effort by carpooling on your drive to the race and striving to bring only two (2) vehicles per team.

reg_system.description: Ragnar Trail Relay Hill Country-TX, presented by Salomon, in the Lone Star State will take place on the amazing trails located at Flat Rock Ranch — a great place off the beaten path outside of San Antonio. This venue boasts the perfect balance of challenging, technical running, and rolling trails. Teams of 8 or 4 will conquer a series of three loops while taking in the natural scenic beauty of the surrounding area. The runner friendly single-track winds through groves of Texas Live Oak, over classic Hill Country limestone shelves, around granite boulders, prickly pear cactus, and yucca plants on its way to the ridgelines that look back onto Ragnar Village and the rolling Hill Country. This is classic Hill Country and some of the best trail running you will find in the Lone Star State.Ragnar Trail Hill Country is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Ragnar Relay Austin-TX and Ragnar Trail Hill Country-TX and earn the 20 Gallon Hat Double Medal.
